"{\"uid\": \"www.theguardian.com.-politics-2016-jun-29-frenzy-hatred-brexit-racism-abuse-referendum-celebratory-lasting-damage-Part2\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"action plan.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 12, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Racist cards sent in Huntingdon.\", \"from\": 14, \"to\": 46, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Photograph: Huntingdon Living Facebook  Why this sudden explosion?\", \"from\": 47, \"to\": 113, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paul Bagguley, a sociologist based at the University of Leeds, points to the gleeful tone of the racism: \\\"There is a kind of celebration going on; it's a celebratory racism.\\\"\", \"from\": 114, \"to\": 288, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With immigration cited in polls as the second most common reason in voting for Brexit, \\\"people are expressing a sense of power and success, that they have won,\\\" he says.\", \"from\": 289, \"to\": 458, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"People have not changed.\", \"from\": 460, \"to\": 485, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I would argue the country splits into two-thirds to three-quarters of people being tolerant and a quarter to a third being intolerant.\", \"from\": 486, \"to\": 620, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And a section of that third have become emboldened.\", \"from\": 621, \"to\": 672, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At other times, people are polite and rub along.\\\"\", \"from\": 673, \"to\": 722, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bagguley stresses that it wasn't racist to vote leave, and that many people were voting about \\\"political control\\\", yet the Brexit campaign's relentless rhetoric about \\\"controlling our borders\\\" has led people who might previously have kept their intolerant views to themselves to feel legitimised.\", \"from\": 724, \"to\": 1020, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A spokesperson from campaign group Hope not Hate points out that, while not all Ukip voters are racists, it does \\\"sw